thetic reactions. The examination of this wide range of topics is far from being completed, and the purpose of this book is to contribute to such completion. It gathers both papers discussing some of Wittgenstein’s most provocative and intriguing statements on aesthetics, and papers bringing out their implications for art critic and art history, as well as their significance to epistemology and to the study of human mind.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAesthetics. 4aWittgenstein, Ludwig. 4aÄsthetik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aArbo, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArbo, Alessandro, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCappelletto, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarsel, Sandrine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDistaso, Leonardo V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerraris, Maurizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallerani Cuter, João Vergílio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLe Du, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeDu, Michel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLescourret, Marie-Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevinson, Jerrold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadilla Gálvez, Jesús, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlaud, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlaud, Sabine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSoulez, Antonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id